5:
Li-Light... Tell the others I said—
G-good... bye......
9:
There are too many people in Starview 
for you to handle all the laundry by 
yourself. I'll go grab the others to help.
14:
Nah, I'm sure they're all busy with 
something or other. It might be time 
to think about hiring a maid to help 
with the chores.
17:
Hmm. Perhaps. There are many 
secrets in Starview, so we'd need 
someone discreet, though.
21:
Yeah, especially if they need to be in 
and out of people's rooms. We can ask 
if the Guild has any 
recommendations.
26:
Welcome home, Milord! Take a seat 
and a server will be with you shortly.
29:
Oh, um, I'm actually looking for a MAID 
maid. Y'know, for housekeeping? The 
Guild directed me here.
32:
Yep, all the waitresses here at the 
Maids' Parlor are genuine maids! We 
offer a free one-day trial on 
housekeeping services. What kind of 
maid did you have in mind?
36:
I guess someone discreet who won't 
gossip about stuff they see on the job.
38:
I'd also appreciate someone who's 
good at looking after others, and isn't 
afraid to speak their mind when there's 
a problem.
40:
In that case, I would recommend 
Dorothea.
*clap* Dorothea!
44:
Wait, she looks younger than me!
...Are you sure?
47:
Of course, Milord. She's observant, 
doesn't like gossip—and she CERTAINLY 
isn't afraid to speak her mind!
52:
Dorothea. A pleasure to meet you, I'm 
sure. Now then, let's get this over with.
57:
You're joking, right? Does this look like 
a two-person job to you, pea-brain?
61:
How many more maids do you think 
we need? ...I figured anything was 
better than trying to do it all myself, 
but this IS a lot.
65:
Depends. Maids aren't cheap, but I'll 
bet you've got someone or another 
here who could handle this with 
magic, easy.
71:
Look at your tiny tub. You'd have to do 
a ton of little loads and keep changing 
the water, while magic could wash the 
whole load in one go—and air-blow 
dry it too.
76:
That DOES sound a lot easier! I wonder 
if anyone'd mind helping...
80:
If they want clean clothes, they can 
pitch in. Honestly, if you have people 
you can put to use, just... put them to 
use?
85:
Why should YOU have to do all this 
yourself? It would take forever to do 
this alone.
...Here.
89:
Drink that. Potions and poisons are 
a specialty of mine.
Heh... Don't worry—that one's safe. It'll 
give you more energy.
92:
Huh? Isn't this just a free trial? I'd feel 
bad taking a potion for free…
97:
I still get paid, you know? Besides, 
I can't have you collapsing on me—for 
my sake.
102:
I'm supposed to provide "exceptional 
service that goes above and beyond" 
and all that garbage. I'd prefer not to 
soil my positively glowing track record.
106:
It looks like you were trying to sort 
everything, huh? Darks, lights, knits, 
delicates...
110:
Yeah! I want to take proper care of all 
the clothes, but everyone dumps them 
in the same basket, so I have to sort it 
myself.
115:
Get that aaaaall the time. People act 
like a wool skirt is the same as a silk 
blouse, but get mad if you DARE wash 
ladies' garments with men's, as if they 
have "cooties."
121:
Oh, I know, right? I mean, I get not 
wanting stuff washed with Nimbus' 
stinky undies, but Light's shirt? C'mon. 
He's a bunny!
125:
(Why am I always so blunt? This place 
seems nice, but there's no way he's 
gonna hire me after I bossed him 
around all day.)
129:
Well, that's it for your free trial. What 
do you think? Should I come back 
tomorrow, or do you wanna try 
someone else?
133:
Hmm... I wasn't really sure about this 
whole housekeeping thing, to be 
honest.
138:
But after today, I can't believe I never 
tried this earlier!
142:
You're definitely more blunt than I was 
expecting, but it was nice having 
someone say all the stuff I don't have 
the guts to. Your critiques were 
completely on the mark!
146:
All the little tips and tricks you taught 
me are gonna make life so much 
easier! You're everything I could ask 
for in a maid!
150:
Would you be Starview's maid? Oh, 
and um, I'd appreciate it if you were 
maybe a liiittle bit more 
straightforward! I can tell you're really 
caring underneath all the sass.
154:
Ca-caring?! Don't get the wrong idea
—it's my JOB to care for people. And 
what's with "maybe a little?" If you've 
got something to say, tell it to me 
straight, coward!
158:
B-but! That'd be rude! I don't know 
where you get the courage to insult 
people to their face...
163: Rude? Did you just call me RUDE?
